				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="1">Random Acts First Aid Camp - Ill Omen, July 22</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:amerygn@hotmail.com">Amerygn D'Arundel</b></a>
				[7/18/2001-2:02:30 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=469204"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
Random Acts will be holding our next First Aid camp in the Lake of Ill Omen on Sunday, July 22nd, beginning at 2 PM Eastern (GMT-5).</p>
<p>
We'll be buffing, healing, supplying food and water, and helping out with those ugly pulls! We also plan to thin out, if not clear, the spiders along the stream in Fironia Vie - assistance in this activity would be greatly appreciated.</p>
<p>
We also plan to have guides/escorts to and from FV and The Overthere, as well as our usual newbie/lowbie aid up towards the Cabilis end of the zone.</p>
<p>
You don't have to be a member of Random Acts to participate - just show up and let one of us know you'd like to help out!</p>
<p>
Why would we do this? Cuz that's what we do!</p>
<p>
Amerygn</p>
<p>
Amerygn D'Arundel<br>
Poet & Adventurer of 25 Songs<br>
Crafter of Fine Armor<br>
Random Acts of Morell-Thule</p>
<p>
For more information about Random Acts see:<br>
<A href="http://www.eqrandomacts.com"      >http://www.eqrandomacts.com</a></p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
				<a href="/NewsAdmin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=469284">										
				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="2">Wheres my Bind Point?</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:xanthus@everlore.com">Xanthus</b></a>
				[7/18/2001-2:01:38 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=469284"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[5]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">Absor responds to a player about finding out what your bind point location is currently at. Here is the post from the <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000243.html"      >Developer's Corner</a>:
<blockquote>
<i><p>
I have several characters that I play on a regular basis. My main two are a Warrior and a Wizard. I'll trade off between the two, playing each for several weeks before switching to the other.</p>
<p>
It seems every time I start to play my wizard again, I forget where he is currently bound. so, I'll gate and find myself in a place I totally wasn't expecting. This is annoying, to be sure.</p>
<p>
My question is, is there any way you can put in a command to identify your character's bind point? Even if it just specifies the zone, it would be very helpful.</p></i>
<b><p>
We recently (well, a few months ago… maybe last year… I don't remember…) added a command that will tell you your bind point. It's /charinfo.</p>
<p>
I've used it a few times since it went in. It's saved me a lot of running time when I've run a long way and then logged off and not remembered if I got a bind at my destination the next time I've logged in.</p>
<p>
Alan</p></b>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
