				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="6">EverLogs v2.8 Released</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:leem@webslinky.com">Curdardh Teyrnon</b></a>
				[7/18/2001-11:03:47 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=469137"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
Everlogs is the log parser that is available with EverTools (<a href="http://www.hydracomp.com/eq"              >http://www.hyrdacomp.com/eq</a>) and will be available through the update facility soon.  A stand-alone install for EverLogs is available at at:  <a href="http://www.gralin.com/everlogs"              >http://www.gralin.com/everlogs</a></p>
<p>
Ver 2.8<br>
* Split out spell information to include both overall stats (like before), and information for each spell.  Damage spells also include min, max, and average damage.<br>
* Added loot tracking and zone it was looted in.
* fix disarm to not include '!'<br>
* Added count and sum of spell damage taken.<br>
* Added Zones visited.<br>
* Added solo and party exp counter (more stuff to me implemented soon).<br>
* Added last name, religion and stats entry the character info dialog.<br>
* Various lists are now sorted (people, faction, loot, zones, spells).<br>
* Fixed bard 'instruments' on character sheets.<br>
* Major revamp of internal UI code.  Makes it easier for us to manage and add new functionality.<br>
* Added second progress bar to reload, shows relative positive in the current file.<br>
* Fix new level message.  Verant changed it in the 6/26/2001 patch.<br>
* Ignore new faction message when it is no longer changing.</p>
<p>
-Curdardh Teyrnon<br>
54 Wizard<br>
Terris-Thule<br>
Guildleader of Dark Omen<br>
co-author of EverLogs</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
				<a href="/NewsAdmin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=469170">										
				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="7">Guildwar on the Seventh Hammer</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:kazanti@yahoo.com">Gmog Dalush</b></a>
				[7/18/2001-11:03:41 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=469170"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
The signs were all there, for any who cared to look.  Yes there were the big signs, the mighty city of Felwithe had been infiltrated for a time.  The Teir’Dal Capital had seen an insurrection as well.  The more subtle things told even more though.  Garrisons being built up, smiths working double shifts, your local merchants being out of supplies.  Ahhh all this and more pointed to only one thing……..  War was coming.</p>
<p>
The forces of darkness, under the banner of the Conclave of the Damned, and the forces of light rallying under Vanguard of Norrath’s banner.  War will be upon the lands of Norrath soon.</p>
<p>
(ooc) The guilds Vanguard of Norrath and Conclave of the Damned will be going to guildwar.  We are guilds on The Seventh Hammer server, roleplay oriented.  The dates have been set for Thursday July 26th, Friday July 27th, and ending on Saturday July 28th.</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
				<a href="/NewsAdmin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=468793">										
				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="8">Epic *cough* Battle for Crushbone on SZ!</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Leon Michaels</b></a>
				[7/18/2001-11:03:33 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=468793"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[12]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
The evils have invaded Faydwer...</p>
<p>
On Saturday morning we had the first organized raid to Faydwer! The evils met up at the outpost in OT and had Merkins, and only Merkins, port the 50 or so evils there (poor Merkins). I found a group as I was awaiting Merkins return from one of his many trips and finally in a few minutes we were inside the Greater Faydark. In my excitement I immidietly seperated from my group and went straight to Crushbone, slaughtering the few n00bs I found on my way there.</p>
<p>
When I zoned in I was surpised at the number of evils there already, there was at least 10. I went straight for the tower, thinking I would farm some easy stuff and sell it for some good cash in Kunark. The tower was deserted so I decided to crash in there for a few before I began my peekaying raid in Faydark. In a few minutes the emporer spawned and I got a DRT, and patiently waited for DVinn to spawn. I got bored after about 10 minutes and decided to go outside, but I realized that the evils had left Crushbone! I thought this was no problem at the moment, since I was easily 10 levels higher than anyone even remotely near me so I camped the zone for a bit. I killed a few unfortunate people and zoned out, and to my horror found at least 50 people camping the zone outside! The lag was incredible so I zoned back into Crushbone, still awe struck at the sight of gathered n00bs. I knew people would be trying to catch me as I zoned again so I headed for the water and swam around for a few. I was sitting at the slaver camp having fun say tunare sux in shout when all the sudden some st00pid ranger tracks me. My MR being like 31 using resistant, he snares me and tries to kite me with his bow, but left me alone after a while since he figured he couldn't do any damage to me (I'll have your head later Oakz :P). I tried to pick off a few people around me but they kept running away, and it was then I realized I needed a partner. I asked my guild and it just so happened there was a shaman around my level near me, so we headed to the spires. Then I had word that all the evils were in MM, so we had no chance of backup. After a full round of buffing we went for the Crushbone zone again. Upon our arrival a small army of about 10 n00bs greets us, and we easily slaughter them by simply having the shaman root then me unleashing my uber kung fu skillz. We killed about 20 people before going into Crushbone and deciding to camp DVinn again. On our way to the tower the shouts started to pick up again, and we ended up being held up in the tower surrounded by people. Sure, we could have killed them all probably but that would have been no fun, so we stayed there for a few and waited for the perfect moment when they all crowded into the tower, then with surprising ease we levitated out of the tower and zoned to Faydark.</p>
<p>
After about an hour of PKing we went back into Crushbone and met up with about 10 more evils. Then we realized all the goods and newts were gone.... I got a little paranoid and decided to check out Faydark and see what's up. About 80 people were awaiting me. Apparently we were being held up in the zone. I spread the word and we decided to wait the elves out as best as we could, figuring about the 11 of us had no chance against the 80 out there. Then the first assault happened. Half of their army zoned in at the same time and zerg rushed us. I had no idea why they didn't use all of their reinforcements but eventually they were driven back out. This happened about 3 or 4 times, still no evil casualites. I told my wizard friend what was happening and he ported in and helped us. All of a sudden I get a tell that the goods and newts were planning an all out zerg rush. I figured this was no big deal so I denied the idea of telling the others, thinking it would lower morale or something. Right when I was thinking this, POW, they all zone in. The spells were flying, the n00bs were dropping, the AoE's were stirring up lag (good job on that one Sage :P) and all the while I never got below 3 bubbles of health, but after I saw my warrior friend get eaten alive by n00bs I decided to zone out. My shaman got her corpse and we decided we had had enough of annoying n00bs for one day, so we bid goodbye to Faydwer and went out seperate ways in TD.</p>
<p>
Good job, both sides showed lots of team work. The evils that helped us in Crushbone were (I think) Higelac, Sage, Punjent, Sektor, Herix, Rathius, Warblade, and Melko (sorry if I forgot your name). I'd like to thank Punjent for helping me slaughter the n00bs, Sage for making lag, Higelac for informing me that cookies are called biscuits in Australia, and Brysion for being my wh*re~</p>
<p>
Below are screenshots of *part* of the battle for Crushbone (there was a lot more of it) and *some* of the corpses of n00bs (there were a lot more of those too :P)</p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=468795"      >Screenshot #1</a><br>
<A href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=468797"      >Screenshot #2</a><br>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=468799"      >Screenshot #3</a></p>
<p>
Pzzak Pkyouthx<br>
31 monk<br>
Vhel'Sith</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		

